Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.46,0:00:18.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ridget...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.78,0:00:21.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, Fleet Commander...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.06,0:00:22.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Take this.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.41,0:00:33.63,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.46,0:00:38.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Take care... of the fleet...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.60,0:00:44.07,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Fleet Commander Fairlock! \NGargantia needs you!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.39,0:00:46.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure you'll do fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.67,0:00:48.44,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.57,0:00:51.42,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You've made me proud...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.70,0:00:56.49,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,When I see your father... I can hold \Nmy head high and give a glowing report.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.82,0:00:58.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Fleet Commander!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.95,0:01:20.55,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.65,0:01:26.08,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Fleet Commander...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.36,0:01:37.19,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Confirming: Earth's coordinates.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.98,0:01:42.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Confirming: Galactic Alliance standard \Ncoordinates from current position.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.37,0:01:45.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously?! It's possible that we can go home?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.61,0:01:48.58,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,To go home, a subspace navigation \Nmethod is necessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.58,0:01:51.23,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Therefore, it is impossible for me alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.23,0:01:53.88,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What? What about the SOS?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.88,0:01:59.21,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,First signal sent since \Nemergency landing on Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.21,0:02:04.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,estimated to arrive in approximately \N6,582 years, 16 hours and 20 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.55,0:02:06.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No... I don't believe it...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.02,0:02:10.88,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Conclusion: Returning to the main \Nforce is effectively impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.82,0:02:14.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't go home...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.03,0:03:49.04,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Separation
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.96,0:03:56.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ridget?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.14,0:03:57.22,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you serious?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.22,0:03:58.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That little girl?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.82,0:04:01.63,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,They say the Fleet Commander \Nappointed her himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.13,0:04:05.11,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe my ship will go along with Flange, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.11,0:04:06.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Shipmasters!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.23,0:04:09.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad I caught you all together.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.17,0:04:12.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I wish to consult with you on the\N matter of Flange's departure.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.98,0:04:14.23,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.23,0:04:15.89,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Now{\i0} is the time to talk about that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.89,0:04:18.19,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Today is Fleet Commander \NFairlock's funeral...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.19,0:04:20.49,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I know that, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.49,0:04:22.44,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You were like a daughter to him,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.74,0:04:25.21,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,and you're not tending to his funeral?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.21,0:04:29.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Fairlock's the one who raised \Nyou after Chevron died.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.13,0:04:33.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.51,0:04:36.90,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You're supposed to assemble at the bow.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.90,0:04:38.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, we're on our way.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.14,0:04:39.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.36,0:04:49.44,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,There is some resistance.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.55,0:04:52.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. I'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.07,0:04:55.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't go home?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.81,0:04:56.79,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.10,0:05:00.35,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Well... I'm sorry to hear that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.35,0:05:05.41,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But if you can't get back \Nhome, you gotta accept it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.82,0:05:08.31,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You wanna kill some whalesquid, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.95,0:05:11.49,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Killing them is my mission.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.87,0:05:15.79,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Then don't you wanna know \Nwhere their nest is?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.79,0:05:17.42,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,They have such place?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.42,0:05:19.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, calm down.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.43,0:05:23.84,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,There's treasure deep inside of a \Nwhalesquid nest. And that means money.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.30,0:05:25.84,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I am not interested in money.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.52,0:05:31.10,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You kill the whalesquid. I get the treasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.39,0:05:32.69,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,How's that sound?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.69,0:05:35.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,As long as I can kill them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.05,0:05:37.44,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Then it sounds like we have a deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.91,0:05:43.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,To release all of the ships that wanna \Nleave, 30 interlocks have to be unfastened.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.71,0:05:46.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a big job, so put your backs into it!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.69,0:05:51.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Flange, won't you reconsider?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.37,0:05:53.87,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,My mind is made up.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.87,0:05:58.46,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,A fleet commander with lax regulations \Nis a ripe target for pirates.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.88,0:06:00.21,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.21,0:06:02.46,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The legacy from the past \Nthat Pinion speaks of
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.46,0:06:06.72,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,has the potential of supporting our future.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.72,0:06:11.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,On top of that, many people wish \Nto leave with me and my ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.02,0:06:18.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I have a duty to protect the \Ncitizens living on my ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.23,0:06:23.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.20,0:06:25.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank {\i1}you{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.63,0:06:26.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Melty!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.47,0:06:29.71,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Amy... Saaya...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.71,0:06:32.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Melty, are you really going?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.38,0:06:33.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.00,0:06:36.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Can't you stay behind when \NFlange's ship leaves?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.55,0:06:39.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I need to take care of Grandpa.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.61,0:06:40.96,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.96,0:06:45.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I never imagined our ship \Nwould leave Gargantia!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.54,0:06:46.88,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm just as surprised as you are!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.09,0:06:51.55,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But, I {\i1}am{\i0} kind of looking forward to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.78,0:06:54.86,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,For one thing, I may meet a boy \NI've never laid eyes on before!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.86,0:06:56.11,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You want to marry into money?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.11,0:06:59.79,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, that's it! And I heard the \Nhottie is coming along, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.79,0:07:00.89,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ledo?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.31,0:07:03.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Pinion's spreading the word
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.20,0:07:07.34,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,that there's no need to fear the whalesquid \Nwith that flying Yunboro around.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.60,0:07:09.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.49,0:07:43.35,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted you to be the next \NFleet Commander, Crown.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.59,0:07:49.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not long for this world. While I'm \Nalive, I need to guide the next generation.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.70,0:07:52.24,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Train her as much as you possibly can.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.39,0:07:59.24,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Fleet Commander Fairlock... I'm grateful \Nthat we made this pleasant journey together.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.50,0:08:03.74,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,May the blessing of the verdurous waves be with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.56,0:09:03.70,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't you gonna change \Ninto your mourning clothes?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.81,0:09:05.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Pinion!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.36,0:09:08.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Sign the departing ship notification.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.54,0:09:10.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop making me repeat myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.52,0:09:15.87,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Then can you prove that it'd be \Nmore profitable to stay here?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.87,0:09:17.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.00,0:09:19.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You got no business tryin' to stop people
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.05,0:09:20.99,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,when you don't even have confidence \Nthat you can protect 'em.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.79,0:09:24.23,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,See you around.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.06,0:10:18.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.82,0:10:20.32,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Saaya!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.84,0:10:23.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.98,0:10:25.99,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You're thinking about Ledo, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.99,0:10:27.87,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I'm not!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.87,0:10:31.84,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen, why don't you go with him?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.01,0:10:36.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Go with Melty on Flange's ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.24,0:10:38.69,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,With Melty?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.69,0:10:43.77,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course I'll miss you, but better \Nthat than seeing you like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.41,0:10:47.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,By the look on your face, I'd \Nthink it was the end of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.97,0:10:51.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Although maybe that's what it is to you...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.58,0:10:56.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing's even started yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.27,0:10:57.96,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Then...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.96,0:11:01.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't! I have to stay here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.37,0:11:02.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.51,0:11:06.83,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't leave Bebel and {\i1}he{\i0} needs Dr. Oldham.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.15,0:11:10.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And besides, I couldn't live without Bebel.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.94,0:11:13.11,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.22,0:11:15.03,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.39,0:11:18.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a relief.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.56,0:11:24.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,After all, I'd be lonely without you, Amy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.51,0:11:27.84,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.81,0:11:45.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like you've got your hands full.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.96,0:11:47.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I can handle it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.60,0:11:50.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, well, why don't you take a break?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.00,0:11:52.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It would set a bad example to \Neveryone if I took a break now!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.86,0:11:57.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.38,0:11:58.77,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.01,0:12:02.99,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Without the Fleet Commander here, \NI've got to keep it together.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.99,0:12:05.70,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I know how hard you're working.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.95,0:12:07.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You're doing fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.88,0:12:10.08,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If things were going fine, \Nthis wouldn't be happening.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.51,0:12:14.08,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,"Fine" and "perfect" are different.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.15,0:12:18.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I went through a period like this, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.71,0:12:21.83,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Back when my dad left me the business.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.83,0:12:25.41,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I was eager to go it alone, so \NI took everything on myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.41,0:12:30.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,One day, I found something huge and \Nwas determined to show off my skill,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.53,0:12:32.58,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,but the Yunboro and I got \Nswept up by a current
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.58,0:12:34.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,and I ended up being \Npinned under by my prize.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.33,0:12:37.23,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought I was gonna die.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.65,0:12:41.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Afterwards, Pinion laughed his ass off. \NHe said I couldn't see around me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.38,0:12:45.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That what I did was the same \Nas not trusting my colleagues.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.21,0:12:51.35,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Trying to do something like this by yourself \Nisn't the way to go about it. So...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.35,0:12:54.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But Fleet Commander Fairlock did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.00,0:12:56.87,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That old man relied on you!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.85,0:13:02.44,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What you have to do is think about \Nwho to rely on, and for what,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.44,0:13:03.99,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,to make things run smoothly.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.34,0:13:05.42,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Rely on?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.42,0:13:09.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You make sure that the items I salvage \Nfrom the ocean floor benefit the fleet.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.10,0:13:13.31,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the kind of person I want \Nto be in charge of the ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.74,0:13:16.90,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm back!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.90,0:13:18.32,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome home.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.32,0:13:21.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry I'm late! I'll get \Ndinner going right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.54,0:13:34.89,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, is it true that Ledo's leaving?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.25,0:13:37.02,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,How did you know, Bebel?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.61,0:13:40.65,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The people in the neighborhood were \Nsaying they heard it from Pinion.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.99,0:13:44.74,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. It's too bad, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.16,0:13:48.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And I thought we'd become friends...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.37,0:13:55.27,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder why he's going out of his \Nway to do something dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.57,0:13:57.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a good question.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.23,0:14:01.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.43,0:14:04.65,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Sis...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.13,0:14:08.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Why doesn't he care about himself?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.21,0:14:14.08,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,At the festival, Ledo looked like he was \Nhaving a good time. He was laughing!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.68,0:14:19.84,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But now, it seems like he's more \Ntormented than the first time we met!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.84,0:14:24.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Even though I'm sure the way he was \Nat the festival is the true Ledo!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.99,0:15:14.23,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,There are people who \Ndecided to stay here, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.99,0:15:19.56,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,How do you intend to deal with the boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.32,0:15:22.77,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to let you decide.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.17,0:15:25.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me decide...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.10,0:15:42.22,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Bebel...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.49,0:15:44.21,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You're going, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.83,0:15:46.74,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. I'm going.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.04,0:15:54.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have to go?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.97,0:15:58.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.58,0:16:01.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that what you really want to do, Ledo?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.15,0:16:05.72,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's to protect the human \Nrace. To protect Amy, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.72,0:16:08.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,My sister doesn't want that!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.62,0:16:17.18,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I want you to have this.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.86,0:16:21.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.69,0:16:23.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's important to you, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.88,0:16:28.07,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,A child who looked like me made it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.07,0:16:29.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,A child who looked like you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.43,0:16:33.84,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Now that I think of it, it may \Nhave been my younger brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.66,0:16:36.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,In that case...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.09,0:16:40.07,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,In the Galactic Alliance, a child \Nwho cannot fight cannot survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.62,0:16:44.75,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It is the fault of the Hideauze, who \Noppress the domain of the human race.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.75,0:16:46.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.15,0:16:47.90,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Earth Hideauze, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.90,0:16:52.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If their domain expands, I am certain \Nthey will make war on humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.39,0:16:55.35,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But the whalesquid...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.35,0:16:57.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,They are Hideauze.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.53,0:17:02.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If things here become like the Galactic \NAlliance, you will not survive, Bebel.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.66,0:17:06.96,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I do not want Amy to experience that loss.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.43,0:17:10.92,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But you're wrong! You're wrong, \NLedo! That won't happen!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.92,0:17:13.52,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I do not want to make Amy sad.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.52,0:17:16.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That is why I will bring down the Hideauze.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.86,0:17:37.34,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Please, wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.10,0:17:58.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I apologize for being late.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.92,0:18:20.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.37,0:18:52.63,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,There's something I want to tell everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.77,0:19:00.03,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Fairlock entrusted me with Gargantia.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.34,0:19:07.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The previous commander thought about \Nthe future of this fleet to the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.58,0:19:10.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to meet his expectations.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.28,0:19:20.49,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to protect this Gargantia that \Nthe former Fleet Commander loved.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.49,0:19:24.31,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to protect this fleet \Nthat all of you live on.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.86,0:19:32.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But my strength wasn't even enough to \Nstop the people who wanted to leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.30,0:19:35.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I am powerless.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.94,0:19:43.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But that's exactly why I want all \Nof you to lend me your strength!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.78,0:19:46.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If you want to protect this fleet...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.97,0:19:53.27,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If you want to protect Gargantia, \Nthis fortress that we live on...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.89,0:19:57.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,...please help me!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.29,0:20:23.74,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't sell us short. We're veterans.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.74,0:20:27.41,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right! When you need somebody \Nto count on, you better count on 'em!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.41,0:20:31.41,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no point in cryin' \Nover the jerks who left!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.41,0:20:35.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You stand in the middle and \Nwe can build a new fleet!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.44,0:20:38.02,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ridget...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.02,0:20:39.52,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That'll do.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.79,0:20:46.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.40,0:20:48.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.57,0:21:03.63,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ledo...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.47,0:21:07.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing there?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.87,0:21:09.23,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.88,0:21:10.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.70,0:21:16.13,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ledo, you're really leaving, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.11,0:21:18.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.77,0:21:22.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Look, I'll hold on to this for you...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.05,0:21:24.22,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So come back for it anytime!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.82,0:21:30.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for everything. May the \Nblessing of the verdurous waves be with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.20,0:22:02.02,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing we can do about it. \NThey've made up their minds.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.32,0:22:06.62,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,They're fools, the lot of them...
